{
  "username": "alice123",
  "title": "Hologram Pop Star Steals Show at Futuristic Music Fest",
  "tags": ["Entertainment", "Technology"],
  "img": "",
  "article": "The Neon Horizon Festival sparked both awe and controversy as a holographic rendition of late pop icon Lila Marquez performed alongside living artists. Using AI-trained vocal models and motion-capture archives, the 90-minute set featured 'new' songs crafted from unreleased demos. While fans called it 'a revolutionary tribute,' critics slammed it as 'corporate necromancy.' Organizers revealed plans to tour the hologram globally, reigniting debates about digital likeness rights and the ethics of posthumous performances."
}
